  "response": "In the Navy, a coxswain is typically a skilled boat operator who is in charge of a small watercraft, such as a landing craft, patrol boat, or small boat. The coxswain is responsible for navigating the vessel, giving commands to the crew, and ensuring the safe operation of the boat. They are trained in seamanship, boat handling, and maritime operations. In some branches, coxswains also play a crucial role in rescue and combat missions, particularly in amphibious operations.",
